## Socket.IO Events

The real-time communication layer utilizes Socket.IO with the following main events:

-   `connect`: (Client-side) Emitted on successful connection.
-   `disconnect`: (Client-side) Emitted on disconnection.
-   `connect_error`: (Client-side) Emitted when connection fails, includes authentication errors.
-   `joinRoom`: (Client -> Server) Client requests to join a room.
    -   Payload: `(roomId: string, callback: function)`
    -   Callback response: `{ status: 'ok', messages: [], room: {} }` or `{ status: 'error', message: string }`
-   `leaveRoom`: (Client -> Server) Client requests to leave a room.
    -   Payload: `(roomId: string, callback: function)`
    -   Callback response: `{ status: 'ok' }` or `{ status: 'error', message: string }`
-   `sendMessage`: (Client -> Server) Client sends a message to a room.
    -   Payload: `({ roomId: string, content: string }, callback: function)`
    -   Callback response: `{ status: 'ok' }` or `{ status: 'error', message: string }`
-   `message`: (Server -> Client) Server broadcasts a new message to all clients in a room.
    -   Payload: `(message: object)`
-   `userJoined`: (Server -> Client) Server broadcasts when a user joins a room.
    -   Payload: `({ userId: string, username: string, roomId: string })`
-   `userLeft`: (Server -> Client) Server broadcasts when a user leaves a room.
    -   Payload: `({ userId: string, username: string, roomId: string })`
-   `roomUsers`: (Server -> Client) Server broadcasts the updated list of users in a room.
    -   Payload: `(users: Array<{ userId: string, username: string }> )`

